                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                              <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <decoDesc>
                          <decoNote xml:id="d1" type="miniature">
                            <locus target="#1v"/>
                            <desc>A miniature of a priest with a <term key="cross" ana="#cross">cross</term> in the left hand and beads in the right hand. Only the upper part is colored.
                          In the left upper corner it is written: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘከመ፡ ተማኅፀነ፡ ቄስ፡</foreign>
                        </desc>
                          </decoNote>
                          <decoNote xml:id="d2" type="miniature">
                            <locus target="#2v"/>
                            <desc>A colored miniature of an Ethiopian round church. Below and above the church there are faces of the twelve Apostles.</desc>
                          </decoNote>
                          <decoNote xml:id="d3" type="miniature">
                            <locus target="#3r"/>
                            <desc>A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> and two <term key="angel" ana="#angel">Angels</term> on both sides who are carrying a scroll
                            on which it is written: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ምስለ፡ ፍቁር፡ ወልዳ፡</foreign>. The faces of the Virgin, Jesus, and Angels are light brown. The garment of the Virgin is bright blue, the garment
                            of Jesus is light yellow.
                        </desc>
                          </decoNote>
                          <decoNote xml:id="d4" type="drawing">
                            <locus target="#78r"/>
                            <desc>A drawing of the hunter with a weapon sitting under the tree on which the bird is sitting. The drawing was published by Turaev in   <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/BVTM8UVB"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:1912Turaev"/><title level="a">Ėfiopskie melkie teksty</title><title level="j">Christianskij Vostok</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Boris</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Turaev</t:surname></author><date>1912</date><biblScope unit="volume">1</biblScope><biblScope unit="issue">1</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">50-61</biblScope><note type="url">bm:1912Turaev</note><citedRange>51</citedRange></bibl>.</desc>
                          </decoNote>
                          <decoNote xml:id="d5" type="drawing">
                            <locus target="#78r"/>
                            <desc>A drawing of a bird.</desc>
                          </decoNote>
                          <decoNote xml:id="d6" type="drawing">
                            <locus target="#78v"/>
                            <desc>A drawing of Barlaam with a rod and two other figures, one of wich is probably an <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/>. Platonov in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/JVEF8BW6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Platonov1996Katalog"/><title level="m">Efiopskie rukopisi v sobranijakh Sankt-Peterburga: Katalog</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">V.</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Platonov</t:surname></author><pubPlace>St Petersburg</pubPlace><publisher>The Russian National Library Press</publisher><date>1996</date><citedRange unit="page">33</citedRange></bibl> writes that these are figures of the bird and the hunter. The drawing was published by Turaev
                            in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/BVTM8UVB"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:1912Turaev"/><title level="a">Ėfiopskie melkie teksty</title><title level="j">Christianskij Vostok</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Boris</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Turaev</t:surname></author><date>1912</date><biblScope unit="volume">1</biblScope><biblScope unit="issue">1</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">50-61</biblScope><note type="url">bm:1912Turaev</note><citedRange>52</citedRange></bibl>. The drawing is partially colored.
                          </desc>

                          </decoNote>
                          <decoNote xml:id="d7" type="drawing">
                            <locus target="#79r"/>
                            <desc>A drawing of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> and male figure with a scroll and a raised arm. The face and hands of the Virgin are colored with light red. </desc>
                          </decoNote>
                          <decoNote xml:id="d8" type="drawing">
                              <locus target="#79v"/>
                              <desc>A drawing of a rider with a speer and of a bare-footed monk with a rod and clothed in a burnous with a hood.</desc>
                          </decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <additions>
                          <list>
                            <item xml:id="a1">
                              <locus from="78r" to="78v"/>
                              <desc type="GuestText"> 
                              <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1199Barala">Baralām wa-Yǝwāsǝf</title>
                           </desc>
                              <note>The text was published by Turaev in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/BVTM8UVB"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:1912Turaev"/><title level="a">Ėfiopskie melkie teksty</title><title level="j">Christianskij Vostok</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Boris</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Turaev</t:surname></author><date>1912</date><biblScope unit="volume">1</biblScope><biblScope unit="issue">1</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">50-61</biblScope><note type="url">bm:1912Turaev</note><citedRange>51-52</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
                              <q xml:lang="gez">ቃል፡ ዘበረላም፡ ነገረ፡ ዖፍ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ሹሐሩር፡ ዘይቤሎ፡ ለነአዊ፡ ሶበ፡ አኃዞ፡ በመሥገርቱ፡ ይቤሎ፡ ለነአዊ፡ ኢትቅትለኒ፡ ወኢትብልአኒ፡ ከመ፡ አመክረከ፡ ምክራተ፡
                              ሠነይነ፡ ዘይበቍዑከ፡ ዘውእቶሙ፡ ዘሀሎ፡ በዕዴከ፡ አ ዕ፡ በዝኃለፈ፡ ነገረ፡ ኢትተክዝ፡ ለእመ፡ ነገሩከ፡ ነገረ፡ ዘኢይከውን፡ ኢትአመን፡ በዘኢቅከሐለከ፡ ግብር፡ ኢትበሪ፡ እገብሮ፡ ወይቤሎ፡ ነዓዊ፡
                            ኢይፌንወከ፡ ለእመ፡ ኢነገርክኒ፡ ካልዓ፡ ምክረ፡ ወይቤሎ፡ ሹሐሩር፡ ፈንወኒ፡ ከመ፡ እርግ፡ መልዕልተ፡ ዖም፡ ዘሀሎ፡ ላዕሌሁ፡ ወርቅ፡ ብዙኅ፡ አንተኒ፡ ትልወኒ፡ እሂዘከ፡ ዘትከሪ፡ ቦቱ፡ ተላዎ፡
                          ድኅሬሁ፡ ውእቱ፡ ነአዊ፡ ወሠረረ፡ ውእቱ፡ ዖፍ፡ ኀበ፡ ዖም፡ ወይቤሎ፡ አምረኒ፡ ኀበ፡ <gap reason="illegible"/> ቦቱ፡ ወአውሥአ፡ ሹሐሩር፡ ወይቤሎ፡ እምይእዜሰ፡ አምሠጥኩከ፡ በቃለ፡ ኂጣን፡
                        በመቅሕተ፡ ዕጽሰ፡ ኢይትረከብ፡ ወርቅ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ጕንድ፡ ወበከርስየ፡ ሐሎ፡ ዕንቍ፡ ሶበ፡ አፈነውከኒ፡ አምረካብኮ፡ ለውእቱ፡ ዕንቍ፡ ዘብዙኀ፡ ሤጡ፡ ሰቤሃ፡ ተከዘ፡ ወፈቀደ፡ የአሐዞ፡ ወይውግሮ፡ በዕብን፡ ሹሐሩርሰ፡ እሞዘ፡
                      መከርኩከ፡ ምክረ፡ ኢተረክበ፡ ላዕሌከ፡ ፩ ዘሀሎ፡ በዕዴከ፡ አጽንዕ፡ እንዘ፡ ሰብአከ፡ ናሁ፡ ፈነውከኒ፡ በዘኃለፈ፡ ነገር፡ ኢትተክዝ፡ እንዘ፡ እንዘ፡ እብለከ፡ ናሁ፡ ተከዝከ፡ ድኅረ፡ ፈነውከኒ፡ ኢትአመን፡ ነገረ፡ ዘኢይከውን፡ ኢትአመን፡
                    እንዘ፡ እብለከ፡ ናሁ፡ አመንከ፡ ከወርቅ፡ ሕልው፡ በዖም፡ ዕንቍኒ፡ በከርሥየ፡ ኢትሃሊ፡ ግብረ፡ ኢፋትለሃለከ፡ እዳዘ፡ እብለከ፡ ናሁ፡ ሐለይከ፡ አሂዞተ፡ ዖፍ፡ በሐወሶ፡ ክንፍለ፡ ወጊሮቶ፡ በዕብን፡ </q>
                            </item>
                          </list>
                        </additions>

